# 🎙️ VoiceBot – Personal AI Assistant

This is a VoiceBot powered by a Language Model (LLM) that can understand your voice, talk back to you, and is designed with data and prompts about me (Aswin). You can interact with it using your voice — like a real conversation!

---

## 🧠 Features
- 🎤 Voice Input (speech-to-text)
- 💬 AI-Powered Responses (LLM)
- 🗣️ Text-to-Speech replies
- 🧠 Prompt-engineered with data about Aswin
- 📱 Streamlit Web Interface for easy access

---

## 🚀 How to Use This (No Coding Knowledge Needed)

### 🛠️ Step 1: Install Python

Download and install Python from [here](https://www.python.org/downloads/).  
Make sure to check ✅ **Add Python to PATH** during installation.

---

### 📁 Step 2: Clone the Project

If you're using Git:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Aswintsidharthan26/VoiceBot.git
cd VoiceBot


##Or simply Download ZIP from the GitHub repo and extract it.

#📦 Step 3: Install the Required Packages
#Open a terminal/command prompt inside the project folder and run:

pip install -r requirements.txt


###This installs all necessary tools automatically.

#▶️ Step 4: Run the App
#Once installed, just run the following command:

streamlit run streamlit_app.py
# Wait a few seconds and a browser window will open automatically with the VoiceBot interface.

# 🔧 Troubleshooting
# Microphone not working? Make sure your system allows browser/microphone access.

# Audio errors? Check if your speaker and mic are set correctly on your device.

# 🌐 Optional: Use with FastAPI Backend
# This project also includes a backend using FastAPI.

# To run the backend:

cd app
uvicorn main:app --reload
# This is optional and used for handling speech/voice features separately if needed.

